RACE.RACE_TEXT: GULFSTREAM PARK RACE 1 1M 70Y All Weather Track CR: 88. Maiden Claiming Purse 32000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 118 lbs. Claiming Price $35,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHANGEORDERSONNY stalked in the four path, bid between foes rounding the far turn, was driven from the four path into the lane, sustained that bid and dueled with the inner leader down the lane, and was up in the final strides. ARAK popped the gate open during the load, but broke well and travelled up close under a hold along the inside around the first turn, tipped out to the three path into the backstretch, bid between foes into the far turn, led into the final quarter, dug in to hold on to the lead and dueled with an outer foe from the three path down the stretch, but was worn down and caught in the final strides to place. COOL MEMORY set the pace around the two path, was put to a ride entering the far turn, lost the lead approaching the quarter, but fought on along the inside down the stretch to hold show. VANISHING INTEREST chased into the two path, was roused into the far turn, angled out to the five path in upper stretch, and was gaining late. MUFRIH brushed with an outer foe at the start, tracked in the four path, ranged up in the five path around the far turn, tipped out to the six path into the lane, but flattened. ENSIGN SKIP brushed with an inner foe at the start, rated in the three path, advanced while tipping to the rail into the far turn, but weakened into the stretch. GUSTAVOR always trailed around the four and five paths.
